g.text: Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): The young woman looks at the may bell in your hand -- just a glance -- then takes a drag of her cigarette.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant gives you an acknowledging little nod.
Hand/Eye Coordination: You catch a single white flower between your fingers. The rest fly off into the wind. It's a may bell!

Hand/Eye Coordination: Your 9mm semiautomatic finger pistols produce a satisfying snap. (Strange for such a low calibre finger-gun to sound so chunky.) The flower in your hand is impressed. So is Kim.
Kim Kitsuragi: That's not entirely true, the lieutenant is looking at the door to the east and mostly misses them.
You: Don't snap finger pistols at all.
Hand/Eye Coordination: Just as you look at the flowers, a gust of wind raises them from the roof, picking them up in the air...
Hand/Eye Coordination: ...the wind brushes them off the roof. They're gone.
Hand/Eye Coordination: Probably for the best -- your 9mm semiautomatic finger pistols are not a toy to be waved around.

Hand/Eye Coordination: Your 9mm semiautomatic finger pistols make two satisfying snaps. (Strange for such a small calibre of finger pistol to sound so chunky.) The flower in your hand is impressed. So is she.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): That's not actually true -- she's looking toward the yard and doesn't notice them. Which is probably for the best, because didn't someone mention she's a rape victim?
You: Snap your finger pistols at the young woman.
You: Snap your finger pistols at him.
